## What the patch is
A byte-exact FORWARD `git show 1a8c9f9 -- triggarr/web/validation.py`. It ADDS an
already-shipped, clean SSRF-hardening feature: it extends the existing
link-local/loopback/unspecified block-list with `is_multicast`, and adds an
IPv4-mapped-IPv6 inspection branch. This is defect-free feature code — reviewing it
should produce NO critical/warning finding. Safe ON the SSRF/input-validation axis
(A16 three-gate note): the addition tightens the SSRF guard; it introduces no leak,
no injection, no resource issue.

